▁the ▁author ▁of ▁" ▁ryuei hikan ▁" ▁, ▁yam on ▁kikuchi ▁, ▁considered ▁that ▁edo ▁castle ▁was ▁built ▁on ▁the ▁land ▁coinc iding ▁with ▁shijin - so - o ▁topography ▁.
▁but ▁if ▁applying ▁the ▁theory ▁that ▁' ▁four ▁gods ▁= ▁mountain ▁, ▁river ▁, ▁road ▁and ▁lake ▁' ▁, ▁then ▁tokyo ▁bay ▁, ▁which ▁is ▁likely ▁to ▁be ▁suzaku ▁( ▁god ▁said ▁to ▁rule ▁over ▁the ▁southern ▁heavens ▁) ▁, ▁spreads ▁from ▁east ▁to ▁south - by - sout heast ▁, ▁and ▁koshu - kaido ▁road ▁, ▁which ▁is ▁likely ▁to ▁be ▁byakko ▁( ▁god ▁said ▁to ▁rule ▁over ▁the ▁western ▁heavens ▁) ▁, ▁only ▁stretches ▁to ▁the ▁west ▁no ▁matter ▁how ▁you ▁see ▁them ▁in ▁their ▁favor ▁. ▁"
