▁amanohashidate ▁has ▁shr unk ▁in ▁recent ▁years ▁due ▁to ▁erosion ▁, ▁and ▁is ▁in ▁danger ▁of ▁disappearing ▁.
▁this ▁is ▁because ▁dams ▁were ▁built ▁on ▁the ▁rivers ▁after ▁the ▁war ▁, ▁reducing ▁the ▁amount ▁of ▁sediment ▁carried ▁from ▁the ▁mountains ▁to ▁the ▁sea ▁, ▁and ▁destroying ▁the ▁balance ▁of ▁sediment ▁deposits ▁and ▁erosion ▁on ▁amanohashidate ▁.
▁to ▁prevent ▁further ▁erosion ▁, ▁the ▁administration ▁has ▁installed ▁many ▁small ▁erosion ▁barriers ▁on ▁the ▁sand ▁bar ▁in ▁an ▁attempt ▁to ▁stop ▁the ▁sand ▁from ▁washing ▁away ▁( ▁in ▁the ▁picture ▁from ▁the ▁south ▁( ▁hi ry ukan ▁) ▁, ▁it ▁is ▁the ▁part ▁on ▁the ▁right ▁where ▁the ▁beach ▁is ▁ser rated ▁) ▁.
▁at ▁one ▁time ▁the ▁trees ▁were ▁bl ighted ▁by ▁pine ▁we ev ils ▁, ▁and ▁were ▁in ▁danger ▁of ▁being ▁wiped ▁out ▁.
▁since ▁then ▁a ▁pest ▁eradication ▁program ▁has ▁been ▁implemented ▁and ▁the ▁problem ▁is ▁currently ▁in ▁ab atement ▁.
