▁buddhas ▁that ▁are ▁forcibly ▁linked ▁to ▁shinto ▁gods ▁are ▁different ▁from ▁religion ▁to ▁religion ▁, ▁faith ▁to ▁faith ▁, ▁temple ▁to ▁temple ▁and ▁shrine ▁to ▁shrine ▁.
▁although ▁the ▁most ▁popular ▁buddhist ▁title ▁granted ▁to ▁japanese ▁gods ▁is ▁bosatsu ▁( ▁bodhisattva ▁) ▁, ▁some ▁of ▁them -- like ▁hachiman ▁daibosatsu ▁, ▁whose ▁honchi butsu ▁title ▁is ▁amida ▁nyorai ▁( ▁amitabha ▁) ▁-- car ry ▁a ▁honchi butsu ▁title ▁that ▁differs ▁from ▁the ▁corresponding ▁buddhist ▁title ▁.
